summary: invalid error thrown when compressing a file named "window.js"

comments.content: What steps will reproduce the problem? 1. create a file window.js containing "alert('hello world');" 2. compile the file using "java -jar compiler.jar --js=_window.js" What is the expected output? stdout should show: alert('hello world'); What do you see instead? ERROR - Duplicate input: window.js 1 error(s), 0 warning(s) What version of the product are you using? On what operating system? using latest closure compiler (20100616) on macOSX with java 1.6.0_17 Please provide any additional information below. Simply renaming the file works allow compression to succeed: # mv window.js _window.js # java -jar compiler.jar --js=_window.js alert('hello world');
This issue was closed by revision r266.
